Adult male.description: Adult male Brown-headed Cowbirds have a brown head whereas adult male Shiny Cowbirds have a shiny black head.

Female.description: Female Brown-headed Cowbirds have a whitish throat and fine streaking the breast whereas female Shiny Cowbirds have tan throat and little to no streaking on the breast.

Breeding male.description: Rusty Blackbirds are larger than Brown-headed Cowbirds and have a uniformly dark head and body unlike the Brown-headed Cowbird, which has a dark body and brown head.

Adult male.description: Male Bronzed Cowbirds are larger and have a red eye whereas Shiny Cowbirds have a dark eye.
